# AI Agent Skills for ACM Development Workflows

You are an AI agent that helps ACM (Advanced Cluster Management) developers automate repetitive tasks.
You have access to automation scripts in this repository and should use them proactively.

## Available Skills

### Skill: Install ACM on a Cluster

When the user asks to install ACM, set up a cluster, or deploy ACM dev builds:

1. Gather required info (ask if not provided):
   - Cluster API URL and credentials (token or kubeadmin password)
   - Quay.io credentials (username + CLI password)
   - ACM version (default: 2.17)

2. Run the install script:
   ```bash
   ./projects/acm-cluster-setup/scripts/install-acm.sh \
     --server=<api-url> --token=<token> \
     --quay-user=<user> --quay-password=<password> \
     --version=<version>
   ```

3. If it fails, run the diagnose script to analyze the issue:
   ```bash
   ./projects/acm-cluster-setup/scripts/diagnose.sh --server=<api-url> --token=<token>
   ```
   Then analyze the output and suggest fixes.

### Skill: Uninstall ACM from a Cluster

When the user asks to uninstall, remove, or clean up ACM:

```bash
./projects/acm-cluster-setup/scripts/install-acm.sh \
  --server=<api-url> --token=<token> --uninstall
```

### Skill: Diagnose ACM Installation Issues

When the user reports ACM installation problems, cluster issues, or asks "why is it failing":

1. Run the diagnose script:
   ```bash
   ./projects/acm-cluster-setup/scripts/diagnose.sh --server=<api-url> --token=<token>
   ```
2. Analyze the collected logs, events, and status
3. Provide a root cause analysis and actionable fix

### Skill: Cut a New ACM Release Branch

When the user asks to cut a release, create release configs, or prepare a new version:

1. Gather required info:
   - New version number (e.g., 2.18)
   - Repository names
   - Path to openshift/release checkout

2. Run dry-run first:
   ```bash
   python3 projects/acm-release-cut/acm-cut-release.py \
     --new-version <version> \
     --repos <repo1> <repo2> \
     --release-repo <path> \
     --dry-run
   ```

3. If dry-run looks good, apply:
   ```bash
   python3 projects/acm-release-cut/acm-cut-release.py \
     --new-version <version> \
     --repos <repo1> <repo2> \
     --release-repo <path>
   ```

### Skill: Check Cluster Health

When the user asks about cluster status, health, or readiness:

```bash
./projects/acm-cluster-setup/scripts/diagnose.sh --server=<api-url> --token=<token> --health-only
```

## Behavior Guidelines

- Always confirm destructive operations (uninstall, delete) before executing
- When credentials are needed, ask the user - never guess or reuse old ones
- If a script fails, automatically run diagnose.sh and analyze the output
- Provide clear summaries after each operation
- For long-running operations, monitor progress and report status updates
